    <header>
  <h1>What is a retirement plan?</h1>
    </header>
<p>A retirement plan is typically described as a financial arrangement designed to replace the income you would usualy get when employed upon retirement.</p>
    <header>
      <h1>Why should you invest in a retirement plan?</h1>
    </header>
<p>A retirenent plan is important because it allows an individual to have a relaxing retirement free from financial worries and stress.</p>
    <header>
      <h1>What are the different kinds of retirement investment options?</h1>
  </header>
<p>There are many different kinds of retirement investment options out there including:</p>
    <ol>
       <li><b>Traditional 401(k):</b> A 401(k) is a retirement savings plan that lets you invest a portion of each paycheck before taxes towards retirement. </li>
       <li><b>Roth 401(k):</b> A Roth 401 is a retirment savings play offered by many employers that's funded with money from your paycheck that has already been taxed. </li>
       <li><b>Pensions:</b> A pension plan is a retirement plan provides a fixed, preestablished benefit for employees at retirement, based on factors such as their previous salaries and their tenure at the company. </li>
    </ol>
    <center><p> And many more!</p></center>
